---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { site } from '../data/site.js';
import { tools } from '../data/tools.js';
const toolCount = tools.length;

const aboutUrl = `${site.url}/about/`;
const aboutJsonLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@graph': [
    {
      '@type': 'AboutPage',
      '@id': `${aboutUrl}#aboutpage`,
      url: aboutUrl,
      name: `About ${site.name}`,
      description: `Learn about ${site.name} — a collection of free, fast and private online tools that run entirely in your browser.`,
      mainEntity: { '@id': `${site.url}/#organization` },
    },
    // Article: marks the About copy as authored, editorially-owned content so
    // Google and AI search engines can attribute the E-E-A-T signals to a
    // publisher entity.
    {
      '@type': 'Article',
      '@id': `${aboutUrl}#article`,
      headline: `About ${site.name} — how we build and verify our tools`,
      description: `How ${site.name} builds, verifies and maintains its free online tools, and the privacy-first principles behind them.`,
      author: { '@id': `${site.url}/#organization` },
      publisher: { '@id': `${site.url}/#organization` },
      datePublished: site.foundingDate,
      dateModified: site.lastReviewed,
      mainEntityOfPage: { '@id': `${aboutUrl}#aboutpage` },
      image: `${site.url}/og-image.png`,
    },
  ],
};
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description={`Learn about ${site.name} — a collection of free, fast and private online tools that run entirely in your browser.`}
  jsonLd={aboutJsonLd}
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-10">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900">About {site.name}</h1>

    <div class="mt-6 space-y-6 text-slate-600">
      <p>
        {site.name} is a growing collection of over {toolCount} free online tools built around one simple idea:
        small, focused utilities that do one job well — and do it instantly, without sign-ups,
        downloads or hassle. Whether you are a student working on an assignment, a developer
        debugging code, a network administrator troubleshooting connectivity, or someone who
        just needs to convert a file format quickly, {site.name} has a tool that can help.
      </p>
      <p>
        {site.name} launched in June 2026. We launched it because we noticed that most online tool websites are cluttered with
        pop-ups, forced registrations, slow-loading pages and tools that bury their results behind
        paywalls. We wanted to build something different — a clean, fast collection of utilities
        that respect your time and your privacy. Every tool on this site is designed with a single
        goal: get you the result you need in as few clicks as possible.
      </p>

      <h2 class="pt-4 text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Privacy comes first</h2>
      <p>
        We believe that using a simple online tool should not require you to give up your personal
        information. That is why most of our tools run <strong>entirely in your browser</strong>.
        When you merge a PDF, generate a strong password, convert an image, or calculate a unit
        conversion, your files and text never leave your device. Everything is processed locally
        using modern web technologies like JavaScript and WebAssembly, which means there is no
        server upload, no data collection and no waiting for a remote server to respond.
      </p>
      <p>
        For tools that do require a server-side component — such as IP geolocation, DNS lookups,
        WHOIS queries and SEO analysis — we use secure API endpoints that process your request
        and return results immediately. We do not log, store or share any of the data you submit.
        Your IP address is not recorded, your search queries are not saved, and there are no
        third-party tracking scripts monitoring your activity beyond standard, privacy-respecting
        analytics.
      </p>

      <h2 class="pt-4 text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Always free</h2>
      <p>
        Every single tool on {site.name} is completely free to use. There are no hidden fees, no
        premium tiers and no features locked behind a paywall. We keep the lights on through
        unobtrusive, non-intrusive advertising, which allows us to continue building new tools
        and improving existing ones without charging our users. Our goal is to make useful
        utilities accessible to everyone, regardless of budget or location.
      </p>
      <p>
        We also do not require you to create an account. There is no sign-up form, no email
        verification and no password to remember. Simply visit the tool you need, use it and
        close the tab. It really is that straightforward.
      </p>

      <h2 class="pt-4 text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">What you will find here</h2>
      <p>
        {site.name} covers a wide range of categories, each packed with tools designed for
        specific tasks. Here is a quick overview of what is available:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5">
        <li><strong>Networking and IP Tools</strong> — IP address tracking, DNS lookups, reverse DNS, subnet calculations, port checking, blacklist verification, SSL certificate analysis and more. These tools are essential for network administrators, security professionals and anyone troubleshooting connectivity issues.</li>
        <li><strong>Everyday and Student Tools</strong> — Word counters, unit converters, percentage calculators, tip calculators, GPA calculators, date difference tools and age calculators. Perfect for students, office workers and anyone who needs quick math or text utilities.</li>
        <li><strong>Health and Fitness</strong> — BMI calculators, calorie estimators, BMR calculators, body fat percentage tools and ideal weight calculators. Simple health metrics you can compute in seconds.</li>
        <li><strong>Finance</strong> — Compound interest calculators, salary converters, profit margin tools, investment calculators and break-even analysis. Handy for personal finance planning and small business owners.</li>
        <li><strong>Math</strong> — Scientific calculators, standard deviation tools, fraction calculators, triangle solvers and random number generators. Useful for students, teachers and engineers.</li>
        <li><strong>PDF Tools</strong> — Merge PDFs, split PDFs, convert images to PDF and convert PDFs to images. All processed directly in your browser so your documents never leave your device.</li>
        <li><strong>Image Tools</strong> — Image compression, resizing, cropping, rotation, format conversion and base64 encoding. Everything you need to manipulate images without installing software.</li>
        <li><strong>Developer Tools</strong> — JSON formatters, hash generators, UUID generators, regex testers, base64 encoders, CSV converters and HTML tag inspectors. Built by developers, for developers.</li>
        <li><strong>SEO Tools</strong> — Meta tag analyzers, keyword density checkers, readability analyzers, heading hierarchy checkers and full SEO audits. Improve your website's search engine visibility.</li>
        <li><strong>Text Tools</strong> — Case converters, text repeaters, word counters, lorem ipsum generators, strikethrough text and small text generators. Quick text transformations for any use case.</li>
        <li><strong>Converters</strong> — Color converters, number base converters, frequency converters, voltage dividers and unit conversions across dozens of measurement systems.</li>
        <li><strong>Time and Date</strong> — World clocks, time zone converters, countdown timers, business day calculators and timestamp converters.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="pt-4 text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">How we build and verify our tools</h2>
      <p>
        Every calculator on {site.name} is built on the same publicly documented formulas and
        standards that textbooks, government agencies and industry bodies use — for example,
        standard BMI and BMR formulas for health tools, IRS-published bracket structures for
        finance tools, and IEEE/NIST reference constants for engineering and physics tools. We do
        not invent our own formulas: each calculator is checked against known reference values
        (worked examples with a verified correct answer) before it ships, and we re-verify tools
        whenever the underlying public standard changes (such as an annual tax bracket update).
      </p>
      <p>
        Tools in sensitive categories — Health, Finance, Islamic, Construction, Engineering,
        Physics and Chemistry — carry a visible disclaimer directing you to a qualified
        professional for decisions that matter, because a browser calculator is a starting point
        for estimation, not a substitute for individualized professional advice.
      </p>

      <h2 class="pt-4 text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Always growing</h2>
      <p>
        We currently offer {toolCount}+ tools and we are adding more all the time. Our development
        roadmap is driven by user feedback and real-world demand. When someone suggests a tool
        that does not yet exist, we evaluate it, build it and ship it — often within days. Have
        an idea for a tool you wish existed? We would love to hear it. Drop us a line on our
        <a href="/contact" class="font-medium text-indigo-600 hover:underline">contact page</a>
        and let us know what you need.
      </p>
      <p>
        We also regularly update existing tools to improve accuracy, add new features and fix any
        issues reported by our users. If you notice a bug or have a suggestion for how a tool
        could work better, please reach out. Community feedback is the single biggest factor in
        making {site.name} more useful for everyone.
      </p>

      <h2 class="pt-4 text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Built with modern technology</h2>
      <p>
        {site.name} is built using modern web technologies to ensure speed, reliability and
        cross-device compatibility. The site is designed to work on desktops, tablets and mobile
        phones without requiring you to install anything. Pages load quickly, tools respond
        instantly and the interface adapts to any screen size. We use a lightweight framework
        to generate static pages that are served through a global content delivery network,
        ensuring fast load times no matter where you are in the world.
      </p>
      <p>
        For server-side functionality, we use edge computing infrastructure that processes API
        requests close to the user, minimizing latency and maximizing responsiveness. This means
        tools like IP tracking, DNS lookups and SEO analysis return results in milliseconds
        rather than seconds.
      </p>

      <h2 class="pt-4 text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Our mission</h2>
      <p>
        The internet is full of useful tools, but finding a good one that is fast, free and
        private is surprisingly difficult. Most alternatives are overloaded with ads, require
        you to sign up before you can use them, or quietly collect your data in the background.
        {site.name} exists to prove that it does not have to be this way. We believe you should
        be able to use a simple utility without compromising your privacy, wasting your time or
        reaching for your wallet.
      </p>
      <p>
        Our mission is to build the most comprehensive, user-friendly collection of free online
        tools on the internet — tools that work instantly, respect your privacy and deliver
        accurate results every time. We are not there yet, but with {toolCount}+ tools and
        counting, we are well on our way.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-8 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 p-5">
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">
          Ready to explore? <a href="/" class="font-medium text-indigo-600 hover:underline">Browse all {toolCount}+ tools →</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
